                    <li class="active">
                        Bay Area Genealogy Calendar
                    </li>
                </ol>

                <h2 class="page-title">@ViewBag.PageTitle</h2>

                <p>
                    Welcome to the new home of the San Francisco Bay Area Genealogy Calendar! Every month, a list of genealogy and family history events occurring within a 40-mile radius of San Francisco will be posted. The calendar was created and originally hosted by Stephen Danko on <a href="http://stephendanko.com/blog/" target="_blank">Steve's Genealogy Blog</a> and then moved to the California Genealogy Society and Library. Now it has made its way back to San Francisco, and Sutro Library is excited to be not only a physical hub of resources but also a virtual hub for the community.
                </p>
                <p >
                    With the transition, there are a few minor changes. The calendar will cover events within a 40 mile radius (instead of 75 miles), which still includes Napa, Fairfield, Antioch, and San Jose. Please email <a href="mailto:sutro@library.ca.gov">sutro@library.ca.gov</a> the following information regarding your event: title, date, time, cost, location, and a brief description (1-3 sentences). If possible, please send a Word doc with all events for the year (or as many as you have planned). If events are planned month-to-month, then we ask that they are submitted by the 25th of each month. We want to display three months' worth of events: past, current, and future.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Let us know if you have any questions by <a href="mailto:sutro@library.ca.gov">emailing us</a> or calling us at <a href="tel:+14154696100">(415) 469-6100</a>.
                </p>

